{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17586190","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17586190"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:28:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:28:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15074"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15074","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15074"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.11,0.6,0.11,0.06,0.11]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7762"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64416"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7762","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7762"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15074"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49848"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7415"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18945"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18948"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21224"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64416","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64416"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EInguinal hernias are a common condition where abdominal contents protrude through a weak spot in the abdominal wall. \u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is correct regarding direct inguinal hernias?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Commonly enters the scrotum","Directly penetrates the wall of the inguinal canal","Is congenital in origin","Occurs more frequently in women","Passes through the deep inguinal ring"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EDirect inguinal hernias occur due to a weakness in the anterior abdominal wall, where there is a \u003Cstrong\u003Edirect penetration into the posterior wall of the inguinal canal\u003C/strong\u003E. This is in the regional of the inguinal triangle. This is an area bounded by the inferior epigastric vessels, the lateral border of the rectus abdominis muscle, and the inguinal ligament.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnlike indirect inguinal hernias, direct inguinal hernias do not typically \u003Cstrong\u003Eenter the scrotum\u003C/strong\u003E and are acquired rather than congenital. They do not \u003Cstrong\u003Epass through the deep inguinal ring\u003C/strong\u003E and are more common in men than in \u003Cstrong\u003Ewomen\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Direct inguinal hernias occur due to a weakness in the anterior abdominal wall, specifically in the inguinal triangle.","Direct inguinal hernias are less likely to enter the scrotum compared to indirect inguinal hernias."],"references":["\u00d6berg S, Andresen K, Rosenberg J. Etiology of Inguinal Hernias: A Comprehensive Review. Front Surg. 2017 Sep 22;4:52. doi: 10.3389/fsurg.2017.00052. PMID: 29018803; PMCID: PMC5614933.","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49848"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15074"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"49848","links":{"self":"https://ap